  "prompt": "What are the type of questions which belong to human behavior topic and not to human nature topic?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of questions that would typically belong to human behavior rather than human nature:\n\nHuman Behavior Questions:\n1. Social interaction-specific questions\n- How do people communicate in different social settings?\n- What social cues influence group dynamics?\n- How do individuals adapt their behavior in different environments?\n\n2. Learned response questions\n- How do people react to specific workplace scenarios?\n- What strategies do individuals use to manage stress?\n- How do cultural contexts shape behavioral responses?\n\n3. Situational decision-making questions\n- How do people make choices under pressure?\n- What factors influence decision-making in complex scenarios?\n- How do personal experiences impact behavioral choices?\n\n4. Psychological motivation questions\n- What drives specific behavioral patterns?\n- How do external incentives influence individual actions?\n- What psychological mechanisms trigger certain responses?\n\n5. Contextual behavioral questions\n- How do people behave in professional vs. personal settings?\n- What determines behavioral variations across different social contexts?\n- How do institutional environments shape behavioral patterns?\n\nIn contrast, human nature questions would focus more on universal, inherent characteristics common across all humans, such as fundamental emotional responses, basic survival instincts, or core psychological traits that transcend specific contexts.",
